Title : Bjørn Atle Holter-Hovind
Text : [[File:Se hva som skjedde 20 år med TV 2 (7176143432) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Bjørn Atle Holter-Hovind, 2012]]
'''Bjørn Atle Holter-Hovind''' (born 14 April 1944) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] media and corporate executive.
    
He was born in [[Oslo]] and has the [[siviløkonom|siv.øk.]] degree.<ref name=snl/> In the 1970s he worked in the insurance company [[Storebrand|Storebrand-Norden]], in the [[Ministry of Trade and Industry (Norway)|Ministry of Industry]] and the [[Ministry of Trade and Shipping|Ministry of Trade]].<ref name=ntb93/> He was the chief executive of Custos Finans from 1979 to 1986 and [[TV 2 (Norway)|TV 2]] from 1991 to 1993.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Bjørn Atle Holter-Hovind|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://snl.no/Bj%C3%B8rn_Atle_Holter-Hovind|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref> He has also chaired ''[[Aftenposten]]'' and [[Schibsted]].<ref name=ntb93>{{cite news|title=Navn i nyhetene: Bjørn Atle Holter-Hovind|date=18 January 1993|language=Norwegian|publisher=Norwegian News Agency}}</ref>

He is married and resides in [[Setskog]].<ref name=ntb93/>

